notes.note:
Customer emailed disputing the declined, unauthorized repair done at Jaguar.
His email:
Hello,

I just spoke with you manager, Adam, at Canada General saying that our claim will not be covered as the repairs needed to be authorized by a representative there. Your office was not open at the time my car broke down (the engine overheated and it was unsafe to drive). I'm a trucker, I work late nights and start early mornings. Unlike Canada General, I don't work regular office hours. Jaguar Land Rover Brampton is the dealership where I regularly service my SUV. I took it there, left it overnight to be fixed. 

We have the pinnacle protection plan. There are no terms and conditions on the paperwork stating that you need to be contacted ahead of time for a warranty claim. All it says is for information/claims/transfer: please contact Canada General Warranty... All repairs that were done were covered items under your protection plan. We paid for the warranty, the money was accepted, and a contract was bound. The dealership where the repairs were performed is registered with OMVIC. What I fail to understand is their mechanic has stated what the issues are, the repairs would need to be done to ensure the vehicle is safe to drive. So ultimately the question remains, why is my work not being covered? Just because no one said yes to repairs that needed to be done anyways?

Kindly provide us with your refusal in writing so we may have it for our records, as this is a clear breach of contract. 

Thank you,
Gurmit Toor

My Reply:
Thank you for your email.
Whist I agree that our office may not have been open at the time of the breakdown, it most certainly was open before the repair was initiated.

The warranty contract does indeed state that you must call our office prior to repairs being performed. Under the section Events That Are Not Covered By This Warranty Letter.
7. any reimbursements where the Company have not been contacted prior to the commencement of repairs or repairs where the Company have not issued a work authorization number;  
And under MAKING A REIMBURSEMENT REQUEST 
 All reimbursement requests must be authorized before the commencement of any repairs. The Authorized repairer should obtain an authorization code from the Company within 24 hours of the Vehicle being received from the Owner for repair.

By having repairs done without the involvement of Canada General, you have taken away out ability to investigate the claim.

I'm sorry we cannot be of assistance with this repair as unauthorized repairs are not acceptable.

Respectfully,
Adam Halko
